00:29:56.380 --> 00:29:59.410
So I have to fairly
unrelated questions.

00:29:59.410 --> 00:30:02.320
One is you mentioned at the
beginning that leaders would,

00:30:02.320 --> 00:30:05.840
or managers, would see their
authority-- power of control

00:30:05.840 --> 00:30:10.230
to the constitution-- what
would their role then entail?

00:30:10.230 --> 00:30:13.230
BRIAN ROBERTSON: Yes, this is
one of the great challenges

00:30:13.230 --> 00:30:16.810
and changes that
companies sort through.

00:30:16.810 --> 00:30:18.220
And it's not easy.

00:30:18.220 --> 00:30:20.670
So imagine you're a manager.

00:30:20.670 --> 00:30:23.880
You've climbed the rungs
in that corporate ladder.

00:30:23.880 --> 00:30:25.600
You've got a bunch
of direct reports.

00:30:25.600 --> 00:30:28.800
And, suddenly, there is a
system that bakes management

00:30:28.800 --> 00:30:30.580
in as just a process
that everybody

00:30:30.580 --> 00:30:32.120
engages in to some degree.

00:30:32.120 --> 00:30:34.970
And you don't need a
manager in the same way.

00:30:34.970 --> 00:30:36.970
What those managers need
to do is make the shift

00:30:36.970 --> 00:30:38.810
to being more like
an entrepreneur

00:30:38.810 --> 00:30:40.020
than a professional manager.

00:30:40.020 --> 00:30:42.910
In other words, how can I
create value in this team?

00:30:42.910 --> 00:30:45.299
How can I actually do something
that needs to get done?

00:30:45.299 --> 00:30:47.090
Catch something falling
through the cracks?

00:30:47.090 --> 00:30:50.060
Build structure so that I've
got the right roles in the right

00:30:50.060 --> 00:30:52.360
processes in place.

00:30:52.360 --> 00:30:55.250
So some of that is similar
to what good managers tend

00:30:55.250 --> 00:30:56.440
to do anyway.

00:30:56.440 --> 00:30:58.810
And some of it is
new and different.

00:30:58.810 --> 00:31:00.470
And there's a big.

00:31:00.470 --> 00:31:03.144
So often those managers end
up filling lots of roles.

00:31:03.144 --> 00:31:04.310
And they are creative roles.

00:31:04.310 --> 00:31:06.726
They are roles that aren't
just coordinating among people,

00:31:06.726 --> 00:31:09.740
but actually getting to build
and create and add value

00:31:09.740 --> 00:31:11.780
in new ways.

00:31:11.780 --> 00:31:13.920
And some people won't
make the transition.

00:31:13.920 --> 00:31:15.420
Some people will
say, you know what?

00:31:15.420 --> 00:31:18.240
I have a staked my self-esteem
on being a manager.

00:31:18.240 --> 00:31:20.550
And I do not want
to let that go.

00:31:20.550 --> 00:31:22.586
Or I've done it this
way for 20 years.

00:31:22.586 --> 00:31:23.960
And I don't want
to learn anyway.

00:31:23.960 --> 00:31:24.920
And they'll opt out.

00:31:24.920 --> 00:31:26.740
And you'll see that too.

